population the expected number of deaths would be 15.8. The relative risk of 
dying is therefore 3.35. There has been no significant improvement with time and 
the relative risk is greatest for female patients.
CONCLUSION: The three main causes of mortality are upper gastrointestinal 
malignancy, desmoid disease, and perioperative complications. Further research 
should therefore be aimed at prevention and improved treatment of these in order 
to improve survival.

